==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[abscessus]]'', a going away, gathering of humors, abscess; past participle of ''[[absedere]]'' (''[[ab]]'', ''[[abs]]'' + ''[[cedere]]'') to go away , to go off, to retire. See [[cede]]

